title: Academic
description: Academic scholarships are merit-based awards granted to students with outstanding academic achievements. These scholarships aim to support high-performing individuals in pursuing their educational goals by covering tuition fees, books, or other expenses. Recipients are selected based on grades, standardized test scores, and exceptional intellectual potential.

new: Proof of Enrollment with the current school
Proof of Income / ITR / Affidavit of Non-Filing of ITR
1 x 1 Picture (to be attached in the Application Form)
300-word essay on why you need the scholarship
renewal: Proof of Enrollment with the current school
Latest Report Card
Proof of Income / ITR / Affidavit of Non-Filing of ITR
Latest Barangay Certificate of Residency
Proof of Identity / Valid ID
1 x 1 Picture (to be attached in the Application Form)

title: Arts and Design
description: Arts and Design scholarships support talented individuals pursuing creative fields like visual arts, graphic design, fashion, or performing arts. These scholarships recognize artistic excellence and innovation, helping students enhance their skills and achieve their academic and professional goals. Awards often consider portfolios, creativity, and dedication to artistic development.

title: Board and Bar Examination Review Assistance
description: scholarships provide financial support to graduates preparing for licensure exams. These scholarships aim to ease the burden of review costs, enabling recipients to focus on intensive study. Eligibility often includes academic performance and a commitment to professional practice after passing the examination.

description: Offers scholarships to students recommended by private schools, recognizing their academic potential and character. These awards encourage continued excellence and provide support for those committed to achieving their educational goals in private institutions.
